author: KATIE GARCIA katlyn.garcia@apg-sw.com
title: 'We needed to do our part.' Scores of volunteers turn out for southside Janesville tornado cleanup
text: JANESVILLE – Volunteers came out to the former Rock County Job Center, 1900 Center Ave., on Janesville’s southside on Sunday, to help clean up damage from a reported tornado that hit the city’s southside Saturday night.
